Photo, Rabbi Harold Schulweis says rescuers of Jews during Holocaust often had 
strong moral teaching. CHRISTIAN SCIENCE MONITOR; Photo, HOLOCAUST HEROES: In 
the early 1960s, Rabbi Harold Schulweis began to look for the other side of the 
Holocaust -- the unsung heroes of that dark period. And he found them. 
Thousands of ordinary people, like John Henry Weidner, above, risked their 
positions and often their lives to save Jews during World War II. 
